1. Download and Install Reference Management Software of your preference

  • Zotero: https://www.zotero.org/download/

  • Mendeley: https://www.mendeley.com/download-reference-manager/windows

  • EndNote: https://endnote.com/downloads

2. Create an account with Reference Manager of your preference

Register with your university email

  • Zotero: https://www.zotero.org/user/register

  • Mendeley: https://id.elsevier.com Enter email -> Continue

  • EndNote: https://access.clarivate.com/register?app=endnote

3. Install the web browser plugins for your preferred Reference Manager

Image: Example of plugin for Mendeley and Zotero in Firefox, it is also compatible with chrome and edge.

4. Install the browser plugin

Open your browser and go to setting -> extensions

  • Zotero Connectors: https://www.zotero.org/download/connectors

  • Mendeley Web Importer: https://www.mendeley.com/reference-management/web-importer

  • EndNote Capture Reference Tool: https://support.clarivate.com/Endnote/s/article/EndNote-Capture-Reference-Tool?language=en_US

5. Create a Web Of Science account Uniurb.it -> IRIS RICERCA -> Web of Science

Web of Science

If it is your first time in Web of Science -> register with email
